{
  "doc_id": "21192",
  "text": "With regard to the nuclear effectors of wnt-signaling, TCF-1 is the only limiting TCF/LEF family factor during T-cell development. TCF-1 deficiency results in multiple distinct, incomplete thymocyte developmental blocks. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] During the DP stage, LEF-1 can partially replace TCF-1 function, since DP thymocytes are completely absent in LEF-1 null mice with a hypomorphic TCF-1 allele. [CITATION_3] In the absence of TCF-1, quiescent DP thymocytes undergo very rapid spontaneous death. [CITATION_4] However, the role of TCF-1 at the pre-TCR checkpoint, where cells expressing a properly rearranged TCR␤ chain normally begin to cycle, accumulate, and differentiate, has not been determined.",
