      "span_text": "TCF-1 deficiency results in multiple distinct, incomplete thymocyte developmental blocks. During the DP stage, LEF-1 can partially replace TCF-1 function, since DP thymocytes are completely absent in LEF-1 null mice with a hypomorphic TCF-1 allele. In the absence of TCF-1, quiescent DP thymocytes undergo very rapid spontaneous death. However, the role of TCF-1 at the pre-TCR checkpoint, where cells expressing a properly rearranged TCR␤ chain normally begin to cycle, accumulate, and differentiate, has not been determined."
